      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HI MANAMEISJEFF NZ (10) took his record at the Menangle mile to 12 from 16 when he led to beat a good mare last time out. Draws wider but has proven multiple times that he can win from wide barriers. Distance specialist who can strike again. CHASE A DREAM NZ (11) was a beaten favourite when runner-up from a similar draw last start but did have to race three wide without cover and only missed narrowly. With better luck he could atone. PINSEEKER NZ (9) raced three wide from the outside barrier but proved too strong last time, taking his strike rate here to 50 per cent. Must rate highly again. JILLIBY NITRO (7) draws lower than last week when he clocked in third to add to a string of wins and placings. Respect along with RIPP (8) who got back on track with a narrow defeat from a similar draw at this circuit and distance last week.",
